data.chText: 要求高的；需要高技能（或耐性等）的；费力的
data.enText: needing a lot of skill, patience, effort, etc.

data.chText: 这工作需要有很好的体力。
要求极严的；苛求的；难满足的
data.enText: expecting a lot of work or attention from others; not easily satisfied

data.chText: 苛刻的老板；难满足的孩子

data.text: difficult ♦ hard ♦ challenging ♦ demanding ♦ taxing ♦ testing

data.chText: 以上各词均形容事情困难、费力、难做。
data.enText: These words all describe sth that is not easy and requires a lot of effort or skill to do.

data.chText: 指困难的、费力的、难做的、难懂的：
data.enText: not easy; needing effort or skill to do or understand

data.chText: 考题相当难。
data.enText: The exam questions were quite difficult.

data.chText: 年轻人要在附近找到工作很难。
data.enText: It is difficult for young people to find jobs around here.

data.chText: 指困难的、费力的、难做的、难懂的：
data.enText: not easy; needing effort or skill to do or understand

data.chText: 在学校读书时我总觉得语言很难学。
data.enText: I always found languages quite hard at school.

data.chText: 这是我做过的最难的事情之一。
data.enText: It was one of the hardest things I ever did.

data.chText: 用difficult还是hard？
hard较difficult稍非正式，主要用于hard to believe/say/find/take等结构中，不过difficult亦可用于上述结构。
data.enText: Hard is slightly less formal than difficult . It is used particularly in the structure hard to believe/say/find/take , etc., although difficult can also be used in any of these examples.

data.chText: 指困难而有意思的、有挑战性的、考验能力的
data.enText: ( approving ) difficult in an interesting way that tests your ability

data.chText: 指要求高的、需要高技能或耐性的、费力的：
data.enText: difficult to do or deal with and needing a lot of effort, skill or patience

data.chText: 演奏这一段音乐需要有很高的技艺。
data.enText: It is a technically demanding piece of music to play.

data.chText: （常用于否定句）指繁重的、费力的、伤脑筋的：
data.enText: (often used in negative statements) difficult to do and needing a lot of mental or physical effort

data.chText: 这对你来说不至于太费劲。
data.enText: This shouldn't be too taxing for you.

data.chText: 指棘手的、伤脑筋的、难应付的：
data.enText: difficult to deal with and needing particular strength or abilities

data.chText: 对我们大家来说，这是一段伤透脑筋的时间。
data.enText: It was a testing time for us all.

data.chText: 用demanding、taxing还是testing？
demanding是这组词中语气最强的，描述任务和经历，常与more、most或表示某方面有困难的副词连用。taxing主要用于否定句，指需要 / 不需要伤脑筋的问题或任务。testing描述经历而非任务，主要与time、week或year连用。
data.enText: Demanding is the strongest of these words and describes tasks and experiences. It is often used with more or most or an adverb that says in what way the activity is difficult. Taxing is used particularly in negative statements and to talk about problems or tasks that need (or do not need) mental effort. Testing describes experiences but not tasks and is used particularly with time , week or year .

means: 需要高技能(或耐性等)的

tr: requiring more than usually expected or thought due
especially great patience and effort and skill
example: a baby can be so demanding

value.def: A demanding job or task requires a lot of your time, energy, or attention.

example.ex: He found he could no longer cope with his demanding job...
example.tran: 他发现自己已无力应对那份劳神费力的工作了。

example.ex: It is a demanding role and she needs to work hard at it.
example.tran: 那是一个要求很高的角色，她必须要加倍努力。

value.tran: 费时的;费力的;劳神的;要求很高的

value.def: People who are demanding are not easily satisfied or pleased.

example.ex: Ricky was a very demanding child...
example.tran: 里基是个非常难伺候的孩子。

example.ex: Her boss was very demanding but appreciative of Christina's talents.
example.tran: 克里斯蒂娜的老板非常苛刻，但同时也很欣赏她的才华。

value.tran: 难伺候的;难取悦的;挑剔的;苛刻的
